template.name: Template App Jitsi Videobridge
template.description:
Jitsi Videobridge Stats. Based on Colibri stats bulit-in api to present Staticis from Jitsi Videobridge.
Full Doc: https://github.com/jitsi/jitsi-videobridge/blob/master/doc/statistics.md

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge audiochannels
item.description: The current number of audio channels.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge bit_rate_download
item.description: the total incoming and outgoing (respectively) bitrate for the video bridge in kilobits per second

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge bit_rate_upload
item.description: the total incoming and outgoing (respectively) bitrate for the video bridge in kilobits per second

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge conferences
item.description: The current number of conferences.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge Conferences with 1 participants
item.description: The distribution of conference sizes hosted on the bridge. It is an array of integers of size 15, and the value at (zero-based) index i is the number of conferences with i participants. The last element (index 14) also includes conferences with more than 14 participants.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge Conferences with 21 or more
Jitsi Videobridge jitter_aggregate
item.description: Experimental. An average value (in milliseconds) of the jitter calculated for incoming and outgoing streams. This hasn't been tested and it is currently not known whether the values are correct or not.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge loss_rate_download
item.description: The fraction of lost incoming RTP packets. This is based on RTP sequence numbers and is relatively accurate.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge loss_rate_upload
item.description: The fraction of lost outgoing RTP packets. This is based on incoming RTCP Receiver Reports, and an attempt to subtract the fraction of packets that were not sent (i.e. were lost before they reached the bridge). Further, this is averaged over all streams of all users as opposed to all packets, so it is not correctly weighted. This is not accurate, but may be a useful metric nonetheless.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge packet_rate_download
item.description: the total incoming and outgoing (respectively) packet rate for the video bridge in packets per second.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge rtp_loss
item.description: Deprecated. The sum of loss_rate_download and loss_rate_upload.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge rtt_aggregate
item.description: An average value (in milliseconds) of the RTT across all streams.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge threads
item.description: The number of Java threads that the video bridge is using.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge total_colibri_web_socket_messages_received
item.description: The total number messages received and sent through COLIBRI web sockets.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge total_colibri_web_socket_messages_sent
item.description: The total number messages received and sent through COLIBRI web sockets.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge total_data_channel_messages_received
item.description: The total number messages received and sent through data channels.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge total_data_channel_messages_sent
item.description: The total number messages received and sent through data channels.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge total_failed_conferences
item.description: The total number of failed conferences on the bridge. A conference is marked as failed when all of its channels have failed. A channel is marked as failed if it had no payload activity.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge total_loss_controlled_participant_seconds
item.description: The total number of participant-seconds that are loss-controlled.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge total_loss_degraded_participant_seconds
item.description: The total number of participant-seconds that are loss-degraded.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge total_loss_limited_participant_seconds
item.description: The total number of participant-seconds that are loss-limited.

item.name: Jitsi Videobridge total_partially_failed_conferences
item.description: The total number of partially failed conferences on the bridge. A conference is marked as partially failed when some of its channels has failed. A channel is marked as failed if it had no payload activity.
